{"word":"H68 - אֶבֶן - ʼeben - eh'-ben - Carbuncle","slug":"H68","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">אֶבֶן</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʼeben"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>eh'-ben"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Carbuncle"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D0;&#x05D1;&#x05DF; - 'eben</b> - <i>eh'-ben</i><p/>From the root of <a href=\"#/H1129\">H1129</a> through the meaning, to <i>build</i>; <i>a stone: - </i>+ carbuncle, + mason, + plummet, [chalk-, hail-, bead-, sling-] stone (-ny), (divers) weight (-s)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H70\">H70</a>, <a href=\"#/H72\">H72</a>"}]}